---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import { servicePricingFaqs } from '../../data/pricing';
import PageIntro from '../../components/PageIntro.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Restaurant Social Media Management Toronto | Toronto Restaurant Growth"
  description="Social and video content add-on for Toronto restaurants — $3,000/month through Jayden Aj. TikTok, Reels, and on-site production. Not included in core TRG plans."
>

  <main>

    <!-- HERO -->
    <PageIntro title="Restaurant Social Media Management Toronto" description="Short-form video and social that fills seats — delivered by Jayden Aj through Forge's content team. This is a separate add-on ($3,000/month), not part of core TRG website and SEO plans." ctaLabel="Book a Free Google Audit" ctaHref="/contact/" />

    <!-- THE PROOF -->
    <section class="bg-white py-16 sm:py-20 lg:py-24"><div class="trg-prose mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <h2>
          We've Already Done This. At Scale.
        </h2>
        <p>
          Most social media agencies guess at what works for restaurants. We don't guess — we have the receipts.
        </p>

        <div class="trg-stat-grid">
          <div class="trg-stat-card">
            <div class="value">500M+</div>
            <div class="label">combined impressions delivered across our restaurant clients</div>
          </div>
          <div class="trg-stat-card">
            <div class="value">598K</div>
            <div class="label">average views per video for Jayden restaurant content</div>
          </div>
          <div class="trg-stat-card">
            <div class="value">113K</div>
            <div class="label">TikTok followers built for @crabboil.ca from zero</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- THE PROBLEM -->
    <section class="bg-surface py-16 sm:py-20 lg:py-24"><div class="trg-prose mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <h2>
          Why Most Restaurant Social Media Fails
        </h2>

        <h3>You're posting, but nobody's seeing it</h3>
        <p>
          Posting a photo of your daily special and getting 12 likes isn't social media strategy — it's digital wallpaper. The algorithm rewards content that earns engagement, shares, and saves. If you're not creating that kind of content, you're invisible.
        </p>

        <h3>You're on the wrong platforms for your restaurant</h3>
        <p>
          A halal restaurant in Brampton has a completely different platform strategy than a fine dining spot on King West. TikTok drives discovery. Instagram drives aspiration. Facebook drives community loyalty. We know which combination works for your specific restaurant and neighbourhood.
        </p>

        <h3>You're measuring followers instead of foot traffic</h3>
        <p>
          Followers don't pay your rent. We measure what actually matters: content reach in your local area, website clicks from social, reservation requests driven by specific posts, and the correlation between content performance and weekly covers.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- WHAT WE DO -->
    <section class="bg-white py-16 sm:py-20 lg:py-24"><div class="trg-prose mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <h2>What You Get</h2>

        <h3>Content Strategy Built for Your Restaurant</h3>
        <p>
          We build a content calendar around your menu, your seasons, your community, and the moments that matter in your specific neighbourhood. No generic food photography templates.
        </p>

        <h3>Video Production & Editing</h3>
        <p>
          Video is the only format that drives real discovery on TikTok and Instagram Reels. We direct, film, and edit short-form video content that shows your food and atmosphere in a way that makes people want to come in. No talking head videos. No generic stock music.
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Food reveal videos</strong> — the format that drives the most saves and shares for restaurants</li>
          <li><strong>Behind-the-scenes kitchen content</strong> — builds trust and authentic connection</li>
          <li><strong>Neighbourhood hooks</strong> — content that speaks directly to your local community</li>
          <li><strong>Event and special promotion content</strong> — drive urgency and action</li>
        </ul>

        <h3>Community Management</h3>
        <p>
          We respond to comments and DMs within a few hours. Every response is written in your restaurant's voice — not generic customer service copy. We also identify and engage with local food accounts that have real influence in your community.
        </p>

        <h3>Monthly Performance Reports</h3>
        <p>
          Plain-English reports showing what worked, what didn't, and what we're doing next month. Reach, engagement, follower growth, and most importantly: which content drove website visits and reservation requests.
        </p>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- CASE STUDY -->
    <section class="bg-surface py-16 sm:py-20 lg:py-24"><div class="trg-prose mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <h2>Real Results</h2>

        <div class="trg-card-dark-accent">
          <p>0 to 113K TikTok followers</p>
          <p>Crab Boil had zero social media presence when they came to us. We built their TikTok strategy, content calendar, and production pipeline from scratch. Within 18 months: 113K TikTok followers, 89K Instagram followers, 500M+ combined impressions, and a successful Ottawa expansion driven entirely by the social audience we built.</p>
          <p><a href="/case-studies/crab-boil/">Read the full Crab Boil case study</a></p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- FAQ -->
    <section class="bg-surface py-16 sm:py-20 lg:py-24"><div class="trg-prose mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <h2>Frequently Asked Questions</h2>

        <div class="trg-faq-item">
          <h3>How much does restaurant social media management cost in Toronto?</h3>
          <p style="color: #4a4a4a;" set:html={servicePricingFaqs.social} />
        </div>

        <div class="trg-faq-item">
          <h3>Do I need to be on every platform?</h3>
          <p>No. We recommend the platforms that are right for your restaurant based on your cuisine type, neighbourhood, and target customer. Most Toronto restaurants get the best ROI from TikTok + Instagram. Some benefit from Facebook for community events and promotions. We won't make you manage platforms that aren't working for your restaurant.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="trg-faq-item">
          <h3>How long before we see results?</h3>
          <p>Local reach and engagement typically improve within the first 30 days as we dial in your content strategy. Meaningful follower growth and traffic impact usually shows within 60–90 days. The compounding effect — where your content is still driving discovery months after it's posted — builds over 6–12 months.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="trg-faq-item">
          <h3>Will you post every day?</h3>
          <p>Posting frequency is based on what drives results for your specific restaurant and platform — not arbitrary targets. Quality and strategic timing beat daily posting every time. We typically post 4–7 times per week across platforms, with a heavier emphasis on the days and times your target customers are most active.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- CTA -->
    <section class="bg-surface py-16 sm:py-20 lg:py-24"><div class="trg-prose mx-auto max-w-3xl px-4 text-center sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
        <h2>Stop Posting Into the Void</h2>
        <p>
          Social media that doesn't drive customers through your door is just an expense. Let's build a strategy that actually fills tables.
        </p>
        <a href="/contact/">
          Book a Free Google Audit
        </a>
      </div>
    </section>

  </main>
</BaseLayout>
